        "System.Description": "<div>ZFNB Tested : DDA Deposit and Deffered Deposit transactions are affected.&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:rgb(32, 31, 30);color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);\">Transactions are passed on as out of balance if there is cash in/out involved and is entered on the Physical deposit ticket before scanning. User has to balance the total deposit amount on the slip with scanned checks on the vsoft scan check dialog to be able to submit. Vsoft is pulled in to find an acceptable solution.&nbsp; See linked user story and attachments.&nbsp;</span></div><br>",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.SystemInfo": "<div>Zeus Teller Test</div><div><br></div><div>When a physical deposit slip is scanned in the Vsoft Dialog in a DDA and Deferred transaction, VSoft will return a value to notify Zeus to NOT to generate checking deposit virtual ticket (credit virtual ticket).<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;display:inline !important;\">Only Pre printed Deposit tickets are allowed for these transactions.&nbsp;</span></div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">This will be a .dll change in Zeus and there is a Vsoft change on this enhancement request as well.&nbsp;</div><br></div><br>",
        "Microsoft.VSTS.TCM.ReproSteps": "<div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"><br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\"></div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">1- Input account number from the deposit slip on the transaction screen.</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">2- Hit scan button&nbsp;</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">3- On the Vsoft scan check dialog select &quot;Physical Deposit Ticket&quot; from the drop down</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">4- Scan deposit ticket FIRST making sure it has any cash in/out amounts accounted for in the total&nbsp;</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">5- Scan checks and Submit</div><div style=\"box-sizing:border-box;\">6- Complete the transaction</div><br></div><br>"
    },
